{title: Blue Ridge Cabin Home}
{artist: Lester Flatt | Earl Scruggs}
{composer: Written by Gladys Stacey and Louise Certain}

[G]There's a well beaten path [C]in the old mountainside
Where [D7]I wandered when I was a [G]lad
And I wandered alone to the [C]place I call home
In [D7]those Blue Ridge hills far [G]away
Oh I love those hills of old [C]Virginia
From [D7]those Blue Ridge hills I did [G]roam
When I die won't you bury me on the [C]mountain
Far [D7]away near my Blue Ridge mountain [G]home

Now my thoughts wander back to [C]that ramshackle shack
In [D7]those Blue Ridge hills far [G]away
Where my mother and dad were [C]laid there to rest
They are [D7]sleeping in peace together [G]there
Repeat #2
I return to that old cabin [C]home with the sigh
I've [D7]been longing for days gone [G]by
When I die won't you bury me on that [C]old mountain side
Make [D7]my resting place upon the hills so [G]high
Repeat #2 x2